name: Sonya C Colon Law Office
about:
What does it means to be represented by a great lawyer who is a Tampa family attorney?
It means you have the dedication of Sonya Colon, who opened her law practice in Tampa in 2008. Family attorneys are a special type. They focus on helping with any legal needs of the entire family.

Tampa Wills and Living Trusts Lawyer

Having a Tampa family attorney means getting the help needed to make sure each spouse has a proper will. Also, it is good to understand the benefits of using a living trust to avoid probate, if one spouse dies. A living trust reduces delays caused by the probate process, saves money, and reduces troubles, making sure life can continue at a critically sad time. Disputes over a will require the representation of a Tampa probate lawyer to handle the legal complexities.

Tampa Real Estate Law

Having a Tampa family attorney means having competent legal counsel when conducting any real estate transactions to make sure all the contracts are satisfactory, complete, and reviewed properly for legal protections according to real estate law.

Tampa Bankruptcy Attorney

Having a Tampa family attorney means when the creditors' demands are overwhelming and bankruptcy is on the horizon, a lawyer is there to guide you through the complex legal process. They help clients preserve what is possible, file the legal papers correctly, and go on to a new life free from the burdens of impossible debt.

Tampa Divorce Attorney

Sometimes divorces are amicable, which means both husband and wife agree to the divorce and how to settle the divorce. Having a Tampa family attorney to handle uncontested divorces saves on legal fees.
About Sonya Colon: Sonya Colon fights for her clients. She knows how to work hard. She worked on her law degree while her husband did a tour of duty in Iraq. She works with the Family Readiness Group, which supports the families of U.S. soldiers and is a member of the International Women‚Äôs Leadership Association.

Sustainable fashion should ALWAYS be affordable for all, and at the Kilo it always will be. Our affordability means we‚Äôre a solid contender against fast fashion (boo!) ‚Äì we‚Äôre just as cheap but without the poor quality, pollution and sketchy labour practices.

We also know that trends may come and go, but kindness never goes out of fashion. We‚Äôve got big plans to partner with some wonderful charities and organisations in the coming months. That positive power may be the best thing we can say about our association and our game. 

"Smashing Stereotypes One Hit at a Time" is the main message of our players and our sport. Wheelchair Rugby is a tough, give-no-quarter game. Our players‚Äô lives ‚Äì their successes and trials on and off the court ‚Äì are a continuous example of smashing stereotypes. The sport is about ability and competitive fire. It is testament to the spirit of our great athletes, their humanity, and the intensity of our game.

When COVID-19 broke out first in China, few people thought it would hit us at home so badly. In late March 2020, our customers in the Government, Defense and Space, as well as Oil and Gas market started asking for support. The name is a statement of our care for the health of all Americans, and our vision for the Company is to become the leader in the fight against COVID-19 and other similar pathogens. Vizocare is our marketplace and vehicle to make this vision a reality.
We are continuously growing our product offering to include a broad range of necessary supplies such as masks, gowns, gloves, sanitizers and dispensers, goggles, safety glasses, and face shields. Vizocare is a distributor and/or dealer to more than 15 prominent US air purifier and filter manufacturers, as well as manufacturers from Portugal and other nations delivering the broadest list of purifiers and and UV disinfection devices.  We are now one of the largest suppliers of PPE, disinfection and purification companies in our country.

name: OpnMkt
about:
The current SDR to AE handoff processes are broken. So we reimagined it and created a marketplace approach to new lead / prospect / opportunity distribution.

Our thoughtfully designed platform changes the way new sales opportunities are distributed to sales reps. Instead of new opportunities being assigned, sales reps can choose them BEFORE they start to work them.

Instead of assigning new opportunities, SDRs list their prospects in an internal marketplace; AEs choose which leads they want to pursue. This model removes the subjective quantity vs. quality and accepted to pipeline squabbles.

Giving SDRs an objective framework allows them to focus on qualifying leads. 

With the ability to choose their prospects that are best suited for them, AEs are excited, motivated and able to connect with their customers on a deeper level.

OpnMkt (Open Market) is more than just a sales effectiveness tool. It‚Äôs completely reimagining the status quo. Sales teams are made up of people; let‚Äôs invest in them like the individuals they are. Put the human-to-human back into B2B and empower your teams to take control of their pipeline and close deals.

100% Salesforce-Native solution available on the AppExchange.

name: Soundbox Music Academy
about:
We offer 1:1 private tutoring for drums, guitar, piano and vocals. Our new studios in Watford have three purpose-built teaching rooms with air conditioning, soundproofing and brand new instruments, designed with student safeguarding in mind.

From beginner to professional, from 5 years old to 105 years old, we offer tuition to suit your skill level, ambition and musical tastes. Learning is done at your speed, with your choice of music, at times to suit you. You can come to our studio to learn face to face, or learn at home with remote lessons via zoom or facetime; or a combination of the two.

If your child is in school, we can provide lessons during the school day in their school, with additional lessons or holiday clubs out of term time.

Our philosophy is to make learning fun; to teach at your speed, and to embed the basics well so you can progress quickly. If you want to take grades we teach the Rockschool syllabus, or we can work with others if you choose.

All lessons are 1:1 with your tutor. We just don't do groups - you learn at your speed, not someone else's.

We pride ourselves on picking tutors from differing musical backgrounds, who can teach not just play, but who also keep current by gigging alongside their teaching.

Open seven days a week, in our own modern studios with ample free parking, we will provide a teaching experience that will get you started or take you to the next level. We have flexibility on lesson times from 9 am to 10 pm seven days a week.

Try a free 30-minute lesson to see if we fit your aspirations.

We look forward to sharing the joy that playing an instrument can bring.

name: Sharp Stone Codewerks
about:
After ten years at my last start-up, I decided it was time to work on my own projects for a while. And thus was Sharp Stone Codewerks formed in the Fall of 2017. The idea was to develop my own products and fund this work with consulting. With over forty years in the industry, having worked for companies as big as Sun Microsystems, Cisco, and Rational to small start-ups in multiple focuses, consulting was an obvious and effective way to go.

The first product was Abstretta in 2017, a dynamic document driven approach to creating and publishing resumes. This core system eventually grew to include a mobile web interface, cover letters, activity tracking, and much more. It became a complete career support product.

In 2019 Bibliogrify was launched. This product is an online bibliography system for content creators that also features peer review.

I am currently developing the Wingate community system. This is a social media network for federated private networks which allows independent groups to form virtual social networks through bi-directional federation.

Sharp Stone is now focused on making these initial offerings commercially successful, while also tinkering with other concepts. There are currently four more products in various stages of development.

All products are writing in Ruby on Rails and hosted on Linux-based platforms. I have been developing in Rails since version 1.X days, back in 2006.

name: Streams & Valleys
about:
The Trinity River belongs to all of us. It‚Äôs the reason why Fort Worth was founded, and it remains our grandest civic space. 

Since 1969, Streams & Valleys has been a passionate voice for the Trinity River. We‚Äôre a non-profit organization that helps to educate our community, raise money for vital projects, improve community access and beautify the River and trails. We also bring together¬†The River Partners¬†and others to work for the common good.

We have decades of progress behind us ‚Äì and now, we have so much opportunity ahead of us with the completion of¬†CONFLUENCE: The Trinity River Strategic Master Plan. As the river evolves, Streams & Valleys is changing, too.

We focus on 5 key areas where we are making significant impact: 
1. Community Awareness ‚Ä®Utilizing strategic communication, education and programming to promote trail safety, water quality and river access.‚Ä®
2. Advocacy and Consensus Building‚Ä®Serving as a trusted advocate for environmentally sensitive development and responsible use of the Trinity River and its trail network by providing a meeting ground for City officials, agencies, property owners, developers, local businesses, and community members to come together and plan for the future.‚Ä®
3. Events and Programs ‚Ä®Developing and producing high-quality, high-impact events and programs to strengthen community cohesion and connections to the river and to obtain a stable source of funding.‚Ä®
4. Special Projects ‚Ä®Managing and coordinating projects that would otherwise fall outside the purview or capacity of public agency partners.‚Ä®
5. Resources for the River ‚Ä®Conducting a wide range of fundraising activities, including pursuit of private donations, grant writing, and sponsored events and programs.

Please join us as we navigate this bold new course to ensure the ongoing success of the Trinity River, our community, and its people.

about:

If you would like to give us some feedback on our products or services, enquire about updating your technology or think there is a way that we can work together then we would love to hear from you!

name: Sexual Health Victoria
about:
Sexual Health Victoria (formerly Family Planning Victoria) is a leading, not for profit, statewide provider of sexual and reproductive health care, education and advocacy. Governed by a voluntary board of directors, we have been providing comprehensive sexual and reproductive health services in Victoria for 50 years.

We provide a range of services which are accessible, culturally relevant and responsive to the needs of the diverse Victorian community. These services include clinical care, education and training to help build the capacity of educators and health care professionals working in the sexual and reproductive health sector. 

FPV's focus is sexual and reproductive health care, education and advocacy. Our vision is sexual and reproductive health for all Victorians and our mission is to provide leadership in public policy, education and clinical care. 

-We are an independent, not-for-profit, pro-choice organisation responsible to a voluntary Board of Directors. 
-We have been providing services to the Victorian community for 50 years.
-We are partially funded by the Victorian Government.
-We also generate our own revenue through fee-based education and training programs and the sale of resources. These funds are used to improve our services.
-We are associated with the International Planned Parenthood Federation (IPPF).
-We value partnerships with organisations committed to the sexual and reproductive health of Victorians.

While our focus began with traditional income producing real estate investments, we have expanded our vision and expertise to include agricultural assets, real estate securities, distressed real estate and development assets.

about:
We are a proudly Mexican company with an international presence. Since 2011, we have developed earthquake early warning technologies and other natural hazards as well.

Since 2014, we have our own network of seismic sensors ‚ÄúREDSkyAlert‚Äù, the largest network in Mexico and with exclusive coverage in the state of Mexico, Morelos, Chiapas and Veracruz.

We are official partners of the U.S. Geological Service (USGS). In 2017 the University of Berkeley selected us to be one of the suppliers of mass seismic alert in California.

Our alerts include Estimated Arrival Time and local intensity which is how strong you might feel an earthquake at the user location.

Our alert service is distributed through:
SkyAlert App
Epicenter
Coming soon:
Mass warning towers
SkyAlert Desk

SkyAlert IoT

name: SpairTime
about: SpairTime is a community-focused marketplace designed to improve the discovery process of local microbusinesses and facilitate purchases of their products and services. Whether you are a local dog walker trying to help your neighbors, or a crafty aunt selling homemade bags to the community, you can be discovered and paid using Spairtime. SpairTime understands that a large portion of small and local businesses avoid building an online presence outside of a Facebook page due to the complicated nature of building a website and growing a Google presence. That is why we made the process of joining the community and listing any products and services for sale as simple as possible. It takes only a few minutes to get started, plus you receive all the major benefits that normally come along with globalized platforms including built-in payments, feedback/reviews, and verified profiles. Rather than prioritizing the greatest spenders in advertisements, we prioritize based on location ensuring that the playing field is level and purchases go to those who are truly local and not just those with the deepest pockets. We are creating a new environment for local microbusinesses to be discovered and earn income like they never could have before.

name: Beat-it.nl
about:
Hoi daar, wij zijn Afuture. Je vindt bij ons de aantrekkelijke combinatie van een enorm aanbod (computer gerelateerde) producten, snelle en stille computers van ons eigen merk en de beste diensten om jou en je bedrijf te ondersteunen.

Waarom Afuture? Klinkt allemaal leuk, maar waarom zou je daarvoor bij ons moeten zijn?

- Hulp waar je het nodig hebt -
Een advies of antwoord op je vraag is bij ons slechts een telefoontje (tegen lokaal tarief) of mailtje bij je vandaan. Kom je er even niet uit dan kun je rekenen op mensen die weten waar ze over praten bijvoorbeeld bij onze eigen technische dienst.

- Je hebt de keuze -
Met keuze uit ruim 1600 merken en 150.000 componenten, randapparatuur en heel veel meer heb je bij ons een wel heel grote kans van slagen. Sla lekker zelf aan het knutselen of laat juist ons jouw droomsysteem voor je bouwen. Kies je √©√©n van de snelle en stille computers van ons eigen merk dan zit je altijd goed.

- Vind en krijg snel wat je zoekt -
Met duidelijke categorie√´n en relevante filters vind je makkelijk het product dat je zoekt. Veel producten zijn bij ons zelf op voorraad en worden daarom vaak nog dezelfde dag verzonden of kun je direct afhalen. Andere artikelen leveren we uit de voorraad van onze leveranciers en ontvang je binnen hooguit enkele werkdagen.

- Ontvang je bestelling hoe en waar je wilt -
Laat je bestelling door ons verzenden naar een adres of afhaalpunt naar jouw keuze. Kies, tegen een kleine meerprijs, zelf wie je pakket mag afleveren of laat ons de optimale vervoerder bepalen voor gratis verzending. Natuurlijk kun je ook gezellig bij ons langskomen om zelf je order af te halen.

name: Sampark Social Organisation
about:
SAMPARK was started in 1987 by Nilesh Desai and his team in Petlawad tehsil of Jhabua district and was formally registered in 1990 as a society under the Madhya Pradesh Society Registration Act 1973. The area was chosen because of the nature and intensity of exploitation of the Bhil adivasis, negligible developmental intervention and the limited presence of voluntary groups. Work was started by addressing the survival needs and developmental aspirations of the people. SAMPARK has since gradually evolved into a many faceted organisation tackling the varied problems of the area and has successfully completed a silver jubilee of formal developmental intervention.
Vision: To facilitate the organic process of change leading to empowerment and development of marginalised communities

The present structure of society and economy is inequitable, unjust, exploitative and environmentally unsustainable and has resulted in the destruction of the livelihood and self-esteem of marginalised communities like Bhil tribals, making them vulnerable and powerless. Change for better can only come about if the disadvantaged people work in an organised manner and actively participate in the formulation and implementation of programmes of empowerment and development. Sampark‚Äôs role is limited to facilitating this organic process of change.
Mission: To facilitate a process through which the disadvantaged and the powerless would organise themselves for a just and sustainable social order and empowered to develop their quality of life, resource, culture and esteem through a participatory and non-violent methods.

name: Stichting De Ster
about:
Stichting De Ster organiseert unieke vakanties voor kinderen van 8 t/m 16 jaar, die net even een steuntje in de rug kunnen gebruiken op het gebied van zelfvertrouwen en weerbaarheid. Hierbij kunt u denken aan kinderen die beter willen leren omgaan met onzekerheid, verlegenheid en met pesten of ze willen bijvoorbeeld leren om meer vriendschappen te sluiten en voor zichzelf op te komen.

Tijdens de vakanties, waar plezier, spel en vriendschap centraal staan, wordt op een kindvriendelijke en leuke manier door een professioneel team bestaande uit psychologen/orthopedagogen, acteurs, bewegingsdeskundigen en allround begeleiding gewerkt aan het zelfvertrouwen, de sociale weerbaarheid en de assertiviteit van kinderen. In een warme en veilige omgeving leren de kinderen van en met elkaar, ze helpen elkaar en sluiten vriendschappen (max. 30 deelnemers, 15 professionals). 

Dat deze formule werkt, blijkt uit de enthousiaste verhalen van kinderen en ouders en de positieve effecten op zowel korte als langere termijn, aldus de Universiteit van Amsterdam (UvA). De perfecte vakantie om plezier te maken, vriendschappen te sluiten en met een vergroot zelfvertrouwen terug naar huis te gaan. Ons team is enthousiast en zeer gemotiveerd om kinderen de tijd van hun leven te geven!

name: BeTheChangeYYC
about:
‚ÄúHomeless Street Outreach - Providing food, water, clothing, hygiene, harm reduction supplies, resource brochures, and referrals. Walking the street of Calgary on foot every Tues, Weds , Sat & Sun 5-9 pm‚Äù

We are a Non-Profit Organization that started as a grassroots initiative summer (2015) in Calgary, Alberta. When we first started as a small group of peers getting together wanting to help the homeless., A few sandwiches were made and juice boxes purchased. A few of that group led by Chaz Smith, who has lived experience of homelessness and dreamed of an Outreach team, saw the need and had the passion to help.   They then decided to make it reoccurring every Wednesday, and then adding a Saturday, and Sunday outreach.  We knew we could make a difference, we knew we could help.

 Over many weeks of research and education, then months, followed by years of hard work. We then grew into a non profit in 2018 that we have today.   We are 90%% volunteer run and funded. We just started by helping one person at a time.  We have grown in our capacity thanks to donations from community members all across Calgary & Area. We are now able to offer assistance to hundreds of vulnerable and at risk citizens each shift of boots on the ground.  This movement is all about inspiring people to be the change in Calgary. Whomever you are or whatever you do for a living you can help. Our group is all about loving acts of kindness to help homeless individuals and better our communities.

Our Mission: 
Through volunteer power we provide tangible necessities, systems navigation & advocacy to help end the cycles of homelessness.

Values:
- Empathy, Compassion, Advocacy, Empowerment

name: Lors Photography
about:
Lors Photography was born out of the vision of two siblings, Laurence and Stanley, and Stanley's son Thomas, who founded the company in 1926 as Lorstan-Thomas Photography in Newark, New Jersey after Laurence mistakenly got off the train from Pittsburgh in "Newark", instead of "New York," a mistake that continues to be made by people even today. Several years later the brothers bought out their cousin and changed the name to Lorstan.

The second generation of the family took over in 1968, and began the expansion of the company into New York. Richard and Steven, Laurence's sons, completed the acquisition of Carol Studios of Long Island in 1991, changing the name to Empire Classics. Lorstan was then renamed Lors in New Jersey.

With no clear family transition to the third generation, the brothers sold the company to Modern Holdings, Incorporated of Summit, NJ in 2005. Since then, Modern Holdings has expanded the reach of the combined companies to upstate New York and as far south as Delaware adding the acquisition of Studio 53 in Philadelphia in December of 2007.

Lors Photography and Empire Studios maintain the consistent commitment to quality and customer service that was the hallmark of the Slutsker business over 80 years ago. Today we employ over 200 creative minds energized with the mission of commemorating the milestones and achievements of the student populations at over 600 schools throughout the Northeast.

name: THE Port Association
about:
THE Port's mission is to connect engineers and innovators from CERN and other institutions worldwide to work on humanitarian challenges that can be solved or improved with technology.

We partner and collaborate with various humanitarian international organizations, such as the United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs or the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC). These organizations are our link to know first-hand about the different humanitarian challenges that are currently arising. We then choose some of them and carefully pick an interdisciplinary team of engineers and innovators that will address them. 

Work on these challenges progresses throughout year, but once a year we organize a 3-day intensive problem-solving workshop or 'hackathon', during which the different teams meet to finally come up with a tangible solution to the challenge. Our THE Port humanitarian hackathon at CERN is our signature event; it allows for an actual transition from ideas to prototypes, resulting in some of the solutions from past hackathons already becoming real products.

Unite innovators. Impact future. Act today.

name: Sonara Health
about:
Sonara Health is on a mission to end the opioid epidemic and save lives! Nearly 100,000 people died of an opioid overdose last year, and approximately 12 million Americans misuse opioids. Sonara Health partners with federally regulated opioid treatment programs (OTPs) to help make treatment more accessible than illicit opioids. Sonara is a patent-pending, remote dosing system developed by physicians to establish trust and add assurance to the take-home methadone dosing process. Sonara provides OTPs with the confidence they need to approve more take-home doses responsibly, to improve quality of life for patients and expand treatment accessibility for those who live farther away from clinics. Notable investors in Mark Cuban and First Trust Capital.

Many patients at opioid treatment programs require daily visits, and most of these clinics are not set up to utilize remote treatment options. Sonara, our first product, is a telehealth platform designed to meet the highly specific needs of opioid treatment clinics and their patients. By increasing access to care for patients, financial incentives for clinics, and savings for payors, our platform will revolutionize the delivery of care for opioid use disorder.

about:
Heicom is producent van bodemverbeteraars en substraten waarmee de meest uitdagende omgevingen - zoals steden, parken en sportvelden - groen worden en blijven.

Vergroening van de omgeving verbetert de kwaliteit van het samenleven. Het is onze missie om steden, parken en sportvelden echt groen te houden, door de kwaliteit van de bodem te verbeteren en de natuur in zijn kracht te zetten.

Visie
In 2050 zal zo‚Äôn 70% van de wereldbevolking in steden wonen. Vergroening van steden en openbare ruimtes in Nederland draagt bij aan de luchtkwaliteit, aan de afvoer van water in een heftiger klimaat en beperkt zomerse hitte. Het maakt de omgeving in alle opzichten prettiger om in te leven en bewegen. Openbaar groen hoort voor iedere stedeling op een steenworp afstand te zijn. 

De natuur is sterk genoeg om voor groei te zorgen op de moeilijkste plaatsen. Als er maar ge√Ønvesteerd wordt in gefundeerd advies, het vervaardigen van hoogwaardige, natuurlijke en duurzame substraten en het juist toepassen daarvan. Daar werken we aan door continu te innoveren en altijd voor de hoogste kwaliteit te gaan.

De verschillende certificeringen getuigen daarvan. Naast de vrij gangbare ISO en VCA certificering beschikt Heicom ook over de BRL 9335-4, BRL 9341 en RAG Landscaping en RAG Green Roof.

name: Spren
about:
Consumers spend trillions every year to look, feel, and perform better.

As a fitness, wellbeing or human performance brand, you know it‚Äôs hard to keep people engaged and motivated enough to reach their goals. Table stakes for consumers are 1) meaningful personalized guidance, and 2) packaged into engaging gamified feedback "hooks".

One option for brands is to spend years and tens of millions of dollars to develop those features, starting with deploying meaningful biomarkers like heart rate variability (HRV).

Or they could just connect to the Spren API.

Your brand and UX stays front and center, while Spren translates complex physiological data behind the scenes into personalized insights delivered in a gamified "hook". These insights create sticky and engaging app experiences with:
- 8-10x user retention and 2-3x daily engagement of benchmark fitness & wellness apps
- users frequently going 500+ consecutive days of use

Spren was developed from over 15 million user sessions, partnerships with 100+ research institutions, and over four billion biomarker data points.

name: TIC Health
about:
The Imaging Centre (TIC) at The Hive London, home of Barnet Football Club, is a blueprint for a national chain of elite diagnostic clinics closer to the community.

TIC offers the very latest in Imaging Equipment in North London hospitals or clinics, all from Canon Medical Systems, and provides a spectrum of diagnostic imaging tests for the most clinical needs. TIC offers imaging equipment not currently found in other local North London hospitals or clinics. 

This includes: 

The UK‚Äôs first Vantage Galan 3T MRI from Canon Medical Systems which puts patient comfort and highly detailed images for accurate diagnosis at the heart of its design. 3T MRI scanners are known to be extremely noisy but the Galan is the quietest MRI on the market, emitting a 63dB acoustic noise when scanning with its Pianissimo Zen sequences.  Patient anxiety is known to be reduced with a quieter scan. The Galan MRI also has a wide and short scanner bore hole for a more pleasant patient experience, which helps to reduce any patient movement, ensuring highly detailed images, which are better for clinical review, interpretation and diagnosing with clinical confidence. 
TIC also boasts an Aquilion One Genesis Edition CT scanner, 2 Ultrasound Suites (an Aplio i- 600 series Ultrasound scanner and an Aplio i- 900 series Ultrasound scanner), and Radrex Digital X-ray. 


Why choose TIC? 

- Open from Monday to Friday 8:00am - 5:30pm  
- 24hr referral process available (or less in some cases).
- Self-Pay referral service available (conditions apply)

- Comfortable, relaxed and non-clinical environment.   
- All services at very competitive prices.

For more information on our wide range of services, a tour of the Centre, or to book an appointment please call: The Imaging Centre at The Hive London on 0333 358 5111.

name: Riverside Business Chamber Inc
about:
Riverside Business Chamber, Inc. (RBC) was formed in 2017 as the result of the amalgamation of Ryde Business Forum, Inc., and Ryde Macquarie Park Chamber of Commerce, Inc.

RBC provides opportunities for its members to grow their business, through networking events, education seminars and workshops, administrative and support services.

RBC represents its members through lobbying to all three levels of government. It provides additional networking, learning opportunities and business tools through its partnership with the NSW Business Chamber.

RBC also acts as a representative voice for the other chambers of commerce who operate in the neighbouring geographical area, supporting and promoting their activities in the community and encouraging inclusion and collaboration between all members of these organisations.

We provide opportunities for you to meet potential partners, clients and service providers. We provide a range of affordable staff training opportunities through our own workshops and those co-promoted with the City of Ryde and the NSW Business Chamber among other organisations. Through our affiliations we are able to put you in touch with IR and HR advisers, Apprenticeship centres and more. By joining us you'll be part of the strongest business organisation in Sydney's fastest-growing business region. Our excellent relations with all three levels of government in our area allow us frank and open discussions with government representatives and the opportunity to lobby on various subjects on behalf of our members.

With RBC membership, the benefits and contacts you will make are manifold. We are a facilitator for business growth in Ryde, Hunters Hill and Lane Cove, and we want to see you grow and prosper.

name: SnapRefund
about:
SnapRefund provides a digital claims payment platform for insurers that sends out payment links automatically after a claim is approved. Our payment platform integrates with your CMS and makes your claimants happier by letting them choose how to digitally receive their claim payment, even at instant speed, which reduces your costs by getting rid of paper checks.

In addition, SnapRefund allows businesses to sync payments to any debit card via any communication channel. Our DIP Technology (Debited Instant Payment) makes it simple. Receive a link via text, enter your info, then receive your money instantly.

This service drives companies' bottom line by improving their customers' experience and retention with an innovative payment flow that serves as a key differentiator from their competitors.

Customer Problem

Money moves slowly with antiquated technology. Whether it's an insurance claim payout, or an ecommerce refund, why not move at light speed? Mail delays, waiting anxiously for a cleared check, and all slow downs in payments are instantly solved with SnapRefund.

Products & Services

We provide a drop in JavaScript widget to our partner companies that can be used in any modern web framework and work instantly. API services can provide enterprise support.

Value Proposition
For Consumers:
- Their money from claim payout is accessible and usable within seconds

For Partner companies:
- Higher consumer satisfaction from the improved convenience of the payout process
- Reduce hours and costs by getting rid of paper checks.

name: Incursus
about:
Our philosophy for a safer community is to simplify one's ability to communicate a concern while streamlining the assessment/management process and create an efficient way to validate the effectiveness of your work. 

Our company's focus is on Threat and Security Management, we have a program for all size organizations or educations institutions, whether it be on our automated digital platform, bespoke personal service program, or a hybrid of the two. Our proprietary management and analytic tools will enhance your current program or act as an as-needed virtual security department for organizations that are in need of one. 

We are the force behind much of the threat and security management philosophy practiced today, as our founders are contributors to ASIS International (American Society for Industrial Security), Association of Threat Assessment Professionals, and Overseas Security Advisory Council. 

Our company of security and threat managers have dedicated more than 30 years to the field of threat and security management and determined implementing technology a necessary advancement to this field.  We put our experience, analysis, and expertise into a simplified software that will streamline your processes in all security/investigations programs. We are up to date with current best practices as we are Certified Protection Professionals, Certified Threat Managers, Mental Health Professionals, and former Law Enforcement Investigators.

Never take threats of physical harm lightly whether you are an individual, organization, or education system. Without the proper training and management program, threats can escalate quickly and evolve into action. 

For too long individuals, organizations and schools have been assessing and managing threats to persons or property without the appropriate tools to respond accurately and mitigate a threat before it is acted on.

We provide a multi-layered software that manages and evaluates cases to guide processes and evaluations.

about:
Welcome to our webpage at www.swedishforprofessionals.com!

Our mission at Swedish for Professionals is to integrate and educate international talent in Sweden by offering customized, flexible and engaging Swedish courses as well as empowering cultural training to companies and individuals.

Our innovative and customized Swedish language courses
Our courses are customized and the lessons are scheduled at your office, to enable your employees to combine language learning with work. We focus on interactive teaching and language that is relevant to your needs; whether they are business-related or personal. With our blended learning approach, we motivate participants with engaging language coaches in class, and digital tools that are used for practice anywhere and at anytime. We develop our course material based on the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages (CEFR) and make grouping recommendations based on our initial online diagnostic test.

Our Swedish culture workshops
Cultural understanding is important in order to navigate professional and personal dimensions of a new life in a new country. Integrating your international employees and enabling them to better handle everyday interactions creates a sense of belonging in the organization. It can also be a way to strengthen your position as an attractive employer in the global market. Our programs help the participants to understand Swedish culture and norms as well as the drivers behind business practices and unspoken rules in the Swedish workplace and society. We unveil the secrets of Swedish culture and empower your employees to fulfil their potential.

name: N-ink
about:
Internet of things (IoT) comprise electronic devices, such as batteries, displays, solar cells and sensors, and is revolutionizing our society by providing radically new means to aid us in our modern lifestyle. 
At their core, IoT technology is typically built up from the merger of silicon chips, providing computation, and a vast array of different dedicated flexible polymer devices, providing sensing and powering. Together such systems enable new functionalities and easy integration with for instance textiles, paper and large area carriers. However, low power operation and advanced functionality require devices that depend on a balanced transport of positive (holes) and negative (electrons) charges. For the silicon chip technology, such complementary electronics is the heart of today‚Äôs digital processors. While polymeric hole (p-type) conductors are being developed to industrial scales, equivalent electron (n-type) polymer conductors are missing. This limits the full potential of many IoT applications as optimal performances can only be achieved via complementarity. n-Ink addresses this challenge, by formulating and supplying n-type inks with unprecedented performance.

Our patented n-Inks are highly conductive, easy to handle, stable and printable. For the first time, n-Ink is offering electron conductors that are on par with commercial p-type inks to bring a new paradigm of printed electronics to the market.
